Main topics: vitality and its levels; vitality management; self-management; stress; regulation of emotions; movement and sleep; healthy nutrition; mindfulness and meditation; flow and nature as sources of vitality.Objectives/eesmärkid:  The aim of the course is to develop and implement skills in the field of self-management and vitality.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  Upon the completion of the course the student: 1) understands the self-management ideas and aspects; 2) understands specifics of human behaviour; 3) understands vitality, its different levels and importance on human health; 4) understands the possibilities for successful stress management; 5) can apply various techniques in self-management; 6) can follow a healthy lifestyle; 7) can implement techniques of self-management and stress management.
